  m_Name: Zara
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::AnimalData
  animalID: Zara
  animalName: Zara
  species: 'Poison Dart Frog '
  scientificName: Dendrobates tinctorius
  status: 1
  biome: 1
  portrait: {fileID: 0}
  journalArt: {fileID: 0}
  introDialogue: 'Oh good. Something big enough to actually DO something.

    

    I
    am Zara. I am also extremely poisonous so please do not touch me. I have said
    this to every animal in this forest and only about half of them listened.

    

    The
    loggers are getting closer. Three days ago they were a kilometre away. Today
    I can hear the saws.

    

    I cannot stop them. But before I ask for your
    help I need to know you actually understand what is being destroyed here. So.
    Quiz first. Then we talk.'
  questDialogue: 
  completionDialogue: 'I have lived my entire life in a ten metre radius.

    This
    forest is not a resource. It is my entire world.


    Thank you for understanding
    that.


    Here. For my new friend.'
  journalEntry: "Journal Entry\nPoison Dart Frog | Dendrobates tinctorius\nStatus:
    Endangered \u2014 population declining\n\nPoison dart frogs get their toxicity
    entirely from\ntheir diet of specific rainforest insects. Remove them from their
    habitat and they lose their poison within one generation. They are a perfect
    example of how deeply connected every species is to its ecosystem.\n\nThey are
    also indicator species \u2014 one of the first\nanimals to disappear when a rainforest
    is degraded. If dart frogs are gone, the forest is already dying.\n\nThey are
    heavily targeted by the illegal exotic pet\ntrade. A single frog can sell for
    hundreds of dollars.\n\nWhat you can do: Never buy exotic amphibians as pets.\n\nSupport
    Rainforest Trust at rainforesttrust.org"
  conservationFact: A single golden poison dart frog contains enough toxin to kill
    ten adult humans. Locals used it on blowgun darts for centuries,hence the name.
  doofNote: I once tried to synthesise dart frog toxin for a Paralyze-Inator. My
    lawyer has advised me not to discuss what happened next.
  questType: 1
  linkedQuiz: {fileID: 0}
  rewardItemID: 
